any tips for a first time esl teacher going to china i am leaving for china in about two weeks i have a job teaching year olds intensive oral english i have never taught and was wondering if anyone had some advice or tips for a first time esl teacher teaching abroad as far as china goes do not expect to be there for the salary i would pick up a few esl related games books for contests before you go and expect highly motivated students keep an open mind and be ready for delays of all sorts in terms of contract and paperwork make sure you have all your immunizations up to date read your country's embassy webpages on travelling and working in china efl esl it is all a matter of semantics imho you will be there teaching english and you will be ok as long as you remember that chinese people do things the way they like to do them whatever problems you may encounter there were not designed to frustrate you personally and don't sweat the small stuff i like to search the publishers and get their books used at alibris Teaching English as a Foreign Language English as an additional language Multilingual Language education Ludwig Wittgenstein Graduate school Education in the People's Republic of China Simplified Chinese character Social rule A Course In Miracles Asperger syndrome Education in Japan Professor Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus Martial art English language American and British English differences Rich Mullins Passport Logic Marshall McLuhan Past teachings of Prem Rawat People's Republic of China Mail-order bride William Perry Confucius Education Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome International English National Football League Patent Bilingual education Criticism of government response to Hurricane Katrina Milton H. Erickson Construction Plame affair Theory of conduct Boston Public Education in Taiwan Avenue Q Education in the United States Tai Chi Chuan Book Supreme Court of the United States Alan Watts Driver's license Who Shot Mr. Burns? Vid